The paper discusses a novel approach for improving handoff and authentication in wireless networks, which is a key issue in the field of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The proposed approach involves collaboration between mobile nodes (MNs), which falls under the category of cooperative networking (cs.CR). The paper also mentions real-time applications such as VoIP, which suggests a focus on multimedia systems (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the behavior of IEEE 802.11 networks, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and system and control theory (cs.SY).
